"v.(用腐蚀性物质或烙铁)烧灼(表皮组织)以消毒或止血 【英】 (用腐蚀性物质或烙铁 )烧灼(表皮组织)以消 毒或止血(burn the surface of body tissue with a caustic substance to destroy infection or stop bleeding) 【例】 cauterize a snake-bite v. 烧灼(用腐蚀性物质或烙铁烧灼表皮组织, 目的是消毒或止血) 【记】cauter读: 烤他; ize表动作－用烙铁烤他. 【记】音：烤烫热灼；同caustic，(用强硫酸)腐蚀（皮肤），会使人失去知觉与感觉 cauterize (v.)  c.1400, from Old French cauterisier, from Late Latin cauterizare ""to burn or brand with a hot iron,"" from Greek kauteriazein, from kauter ""burning or branding iron,"" from kaiein ""to burn"" (see caustic). Related: Cauterized; cauterizing."
